itly listed—a minor gap in searchability.\n\nSpecSheetTemplate.files is technically a separate component from SpecSheetTemplate.xlsx, but since \"SpecSheetTemplate\" as a PascalCase name is already represented, this feels like a minor coverage issue rather than a significant omission.\n\nOverall the knowledge file looks solid, so I'll proceed with my report. The knowledge file drops the server-side context and the reference to incoming requests, which are minor qualifiers but worth noting—the core meaning about cross-field and semantic validation checks is intact.\n\nLooking at the actual attributes though, they're all marked as client-side only, which creates an odd tension with the intro describing server-side validation. But that intro is really just explaining what the tag documents, not claiming the tag itself runs server-side, so that nuance seems adequately captured already.\n\nThe file looks solid overall. I'm noticing a couple of missing file references in the hints—`SpecSheetTemplate.files` and `spec.js` don't appear in the component table hints even though they're listed in the files section.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":14259,"cache_read_input_tokens":18400,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":14259,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"92de4c60-03d8-4cce-9d9f-37a3185f65db","uuid":"efceda64-9070-41fe-b467-c8634a84a8c0"}
